==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acescent
<hw>A*ces"cent</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acescens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>acescere</ets> to
turn sour; inchoative of <ets>acere</ets> to be sour: cf. F.
<ets>acescent</ets>. See <er>Acid</er>.]</ety> <def>Turning sour;
readily becoming tart or acid; slightly sour.</def>
<rj><au>Faraday.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acescent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Acescent
<hw>A*ces"cent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A substance liable to become
sour.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

